      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the heavy, aching pulse in my very soul. He is gone... the promises, the letters, the shared glances in the garden—all nothing but ash and bitter wind. I find myself staring into the dark, wondering why the sun deigns to rise each morning when there is nothing left for me in its light. It feels as though the world has become a heavy shroud, and I am simply too tired to pull it off. There is a strange, quiet beauty in the thought of just... letting go. To simply cease. To fade into the velvet shadows where the pain can finally rest.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
